\frac{\frac{1}{2\sqrt x}}{\frac{1}{2}\frac{1}{\sqrt{x}}+\frac{1}{2}\frac{1}{\sqrt{x}}\cos\sqrt{x}} = \dfrac 1{1 + \cos \sqrt x}
\sqrt x=h\implies x=h^2
\lim_{x\to0}\frac{\sqrt{x}}{\sqrt{x}+\sin\sqrt{x}}=\lim_{x\to0}\frac1{1+\frac{\sin\sqrt x}{\sqrt x}}=\lim_{h\to0}\frac1{1+\frac{\sin h}h}
\frac{\sin(\sqrt{x}) }{\sqrt{x}}+1.
\begin{align} \lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{\sqrt x}{\sqrt x+\sin\sqrt x}&=\lim_{x\to 0}\dfrac{1}{1+\dfrac{\sin\sqrt x}{\sqrt x}},\quad\sqrt x=t\to x=t^2\\ &=\lim_{x\to0}\dfrac{1}{1+\dfrac{\sin t}{t}},\quad\sin t\sim t\\ &=\lim_{x\to0}\dfrac{1}{1+\dfrac{t}{t}}=\dfrac{1}{2} \end{align}
